  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The present study assesses the health-related quality of life of diabetic transmetatarstal
      and below-knee prosthetic user. The study design is cross-sectional with a retrospective
      review of patient hospital records and an assessment with patient-reported outcome measure.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The present study aims to recruit 100 diabetic transmetatarsal and below-knee prosthetic user
      to assess the health-related quality of life (HRQoL) between these two patient groups. The
      15D HRQoL instrument is applied. An additional comparison with the age-standardized Finnish
      general population will be performed.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
